cs.SI, cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.SD, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper deals with modeling social post streams as evolving networks and tracking event evolution patterns in real time.
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also likely as the paper involves natural language processing techniques such as post similarity and word clouds.
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is relevant as the paper deals with information dissemination and event detection from social streams.
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is less likely but still possible as the paper proposes incremental update algorithms to handle highly dynamic social streams.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also less likely but possible as the paper involves constructing edges between posts and summarizing information in the stream using a "sketch graph".
